104
00:06:50,527 --> 00:06:52,859
made me invincible.

105
00:06:52,859 --> 00:06:56,560
But in reality, there were many things
to compromise on.

106
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:59,225
And ultimately, I didn't share
the same vision with my partner.

107
00:06:59,225 --> 00:07:00,794
So, we split up.

108
00:07:00,794 --> 00:07:01,859
Shi Ping.

109
00:07:01,859 --> 00:07:05,293
Won't you really consider staying?

110
00:07:05,293 --> 00:07:08,660
Since our philosophies don't align,
there's no need to force me.

111
00:07:08,660 --> 00:07:09,993
I'll leave the company to you.

112
00:07:09,993 --> 00:07:12,160
From now on, we'll each put in our effort.

113
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,293
I'm leaving.

114
00:07:13,293 --> 00:07:16,660
Shi Ping, can we talk about it again?

115
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:19,192
Later, I opened my own office.

116
00:07:19,192 --> 00:07:22,427
Still with a strong personality,
and was very persistent.

117
00:07:22,427 --> 00:07:24,192
If an employee made a mistake,

118
00:07:24,192 --> 00:07:26,560
then I'd immediately tell her to leave.

119
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:29,626
Did you bring a ruler when you were measuring?

120
00:07:29,626 --> 00:07:31,092
Yes.

121
00:07:31,092 --> 00:07:33,325
Yes?

122
00:07:33,325 --> 00:07:35,794
Then that means you didn't bring your brain.

123
00:07:35,794 --> 00:07:36,927
The measurements for all sizes

124
00:07:36,927 --> 00:07:39,027
can vary by more than plus
or minus two centimeters.

125
00:07:39,027 --> 00:07:41,527
It's not simple.

126
00:07:41,527 --> 00:07:43,192
You're fired.

127
00:07:43,192 --> 00:07:45,459
Director Zhang, can you give me another chance?

128
00:07:45,459 --> 00:07:48,027
Get out.

129
00:07:50,393 --> 00:07:53,393
In the end, only I and the accountant
were left in the office.

130
00:07:53,393 --> 00:07:56,126
I almost caused it to shut down.

131
00:07:57,692 --> 00:08:01,192
One day, I was just sitting by the street.

132
00:08:01,192 --> 00:08:03,459
Originally, I was thinking

133
00:08:03,459 --> 00:08:06,192
whether my dream was too unrealistic.

134
00:08:06,192 --> 00:08:09,427
Whether I should give up.

135
00:08:09,427 --> 00:08:11,760
But looking

136
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,427
at the passersby on the street,

137
00:08:13,427 --> 00:08:15,894
everyone is headed in different directions.

138
00:08:15,894 --> 00:08:17,393
Coming and going.

139
00:08:17,393 --> 00:08:20,225
All in a hurry.

140
00:08:20,225 --> 00:08:22,826
I suddenly realized something.

141
00:08:22,826 --> 00:08:26,060
My dream is mine.

142
00:08:26,060 --> 00:08:28,192
Not my employees'.

143
00:08:28,192 --> 00:08:30,359
They come to work at Bosheng

144
00:08:30,359 --> 00:08:33,492
for their own future and dreams,

145
00:08:33,492 --> 00:08:35,960
and not for me.

146
00:08:40,026 --> 00:08:43,093
So, I shouldn't take

147
00:08:43,093 --> 00:08:46,492
them sacrificing for my dream for granted.

148
00:08:46,492 --> 00:08:48,692
Instead, I should be thankful to them.

149
00:08:48,692 --> 00:08:52,026
And even persuade them

150
00:08:52,026 --> 00:08:53,760
to consider working at Bosheng

151
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:56,093
as one of their dreams.

152
00:08:56,093 --> 00:08:57,760
And make them understand

153
00:08:57,760 --> 00:09:00,060
